  "description": "Decomposed plant and animal material in soil. Organic matter holds water like a sponge, releases nutrients as it decomposes further, and binds mineral particles into aggregates that improve soil structure. Gardeners increase organic matter by adding compost, aged manure, or leaf mold.",
